  m_Name: Family Crest
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Family Crest
  description: 'A family crest was a heraldic symbol used to represent a noble family
    and their lineage. These crests were displayed on buildings, objects, and documents
    to show ownership, status, and alliances. In larger estates, variations of the
    main crest could also represent related families or vassal houses connected through
    marriage or service. '
